Elevate your career in law enforcement technology and join us to make
Queensland the safest state – apply now and make a real impact!

** The core capability requirements for this role are: **

  * Adherence to QPS agreed software testing practice. 
  * Understanding and working to product test plans to ensure the delivered solution meets the requirements and deliverables of the customer. 
  * Assisting in the development and completion of manual and automated test plans. 
  * Liaise regularly with cross functional team to effectively plan and execute testing activities within agreed time frames. 
  * Identifying testing requirement scenarios. 
  * Reviewing and self-assessing test coverage ensuring traceability, quality assurance and quality completeness for own and others work. 

** Role Requirements: **

_ ** Qualification: ** _

** The following qualification is highly desirable: **

  * ISTQB Certification 

** Highly Desirable Technical/ Operational/ Educational experience: **

  * Substantial professional software or test development experience 
  * Working knowledge of test recording tools (such as Azure DevOps, Atlassian Jira) in a business setting including requirement traceability, test lab setup and tool reporting 
  * Knowledge of programming and design in .NET, Java and Python 
  * Substantial knowledge of at least one, self-nominated area of technical expertise 
  * Knowledge of Windows Server, MS SQL, Networking principles, Data Integrity and system architecture knowledge 
  * Test automation experience including tools (TestComplete, Postman, SoapUI, ReadyAPI) 
  * Experience providing product showcases to internal and external stakeholders 
  * Experience writing BDD test scripts and test cases 

** Desirable skills/requirements: **

  * Knowledge of, or ability to rapidly acquire knowledge of, QPS Information Systems in support of Emergency Services in Queensland including QPRIME, QCAD and other applications used throughout QPS 
  * Knowledge of, or ability to rapidly acquire knowledge of, technologies or platforms including Azure, AWS, HTML5 and Selenium 
  * An understanding of testing in the context of ICT as a service 

